      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate clinical loading environment including physiological load magnitude, rate, and environmental conditioning.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed per ASTM F1717 at ambient temperature and displacement rate 25 mm/min. Single test condition only — no variation in load rate, temperature, or construct offset distance. Physiological saline conditioning not applied. Achieved level 2 falls below required level 3; this shortfall is documented and accepted given that ASTM F1717 is the regulatory standard for this device class and comparative FEA-to-test agreement is the primary objective."
