    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed required credibility levels. One factor (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) falls below requirement; this shortfall is accepted because ASTM F1717 is the applicable regulatory standard and the primary objective is quantitative FEA-to-test agreement rather than physiological fidelity. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96; absolute percent difference < 10%) across N=11 constructs at two independent laboratories. Overall credibility is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
